               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500708-name-704" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-704" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-704" type="surname" value="CRISTALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-704" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY CRISTALL</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner has dealt with me and my partners for some years, as master of a vessel—on 27th June he came, and said he wanted some junk to refit his vessel for the Baltic trade—he said he was master of the <hi rend="italic">Eliza,</hi> which was lying in the Regent's Canal—believing his story, he had 1 cwt. 1qr. 16lbs.—it was a ready money transaction—they are all ready money transactions; they take the goods one day, and come next day to pay us—there was no such vessel as the <hi rend="italic">Eliza</hi> there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> I proposed to pay him afterwards? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> After he was in Horsemonger-lane, he sent me a letter.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500708-name-705" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-705" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-705" type="surname" value="DRAKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-705" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM DRAKE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am store-keeper to Henry Cristall and others. On 2nd July the prisoner came, and I supplied him with a quantity of junk—Davis took possession of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500708-name-706" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-706" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-706" type="surname" value="AUSTIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-706" type="given" value="STEVEN"></interp>STEVEN AUSTIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Joseph, William, and Henry Cristall. On 27th June I took some junk to the Globe-stairs, and left it with the waterman, and on 29th June another quantity.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500708-name-707" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-707" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-707" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-707" type="given" value="THOMAS HENRY"></interp>THOMAS HENRY DAVIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a waterman. On 2nd July I went to the prosecutors' warehouse by the prisoner's direction—I took the junk to the Regent's Canal—I did not find the <hi rend="italic">Eliza</hi>—the rope was afterwards taken to Mr. Cohen's, and sold by the prisoner, I believe for 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I saw him handle one sovereign.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
